OL,4,CBirmingham restaurant owner says mask
OL,5,Cpolicy critics are 'nuts'
OL,6, A restaurant owner who received angry
OL,7, emails after asking customers to
OL,8, continue wearing masks has said his
OL,9, critics are "nuts".
OL,11,FAlex Claridge, who runs The Wilderness
OL,12,Fin Birmingham, said he'd been accused
OL,13,Fof "glorified virtue-signalling" after
OL,14,Fhe sent out an email to customers
OL,15,Fexplaining his position.
OL,17,FHe said he was "flabbergasted" at the
OL,18,Fresponse, from a "vocal minority".
OL,20,FBut he said his customers would only be
OL,21,F"mildly inconvenienced" by the rules.
